To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Kentucky Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

January 25, 2023 arrest and custody of Robin Brown, by the Winchester Police Department:

1. The arrest or incident report for this case;
2. Any booking or intake documents, including the time and location of custody, and personnel involved;
3. Any holding cell assignment logs, temporary detention room usage records, or custody housing logs from January 25 through January 31, 2023;
4. Any visitor sign-in sheets, logbooks, or interview room access logs for the duration of Ms. Brown’s custody during that same time period;
5. Any shift notes, watch commander logs, or internal duty officer summaries referencing her movement or custodial status;
6. Any transportation or custody transfer records, including documentation reflecting any handoffs between officers, agencies, or facilities;
7. Any dispatch logs or CAD (computer-aided dispatch) reports reflecting arrest, transport, or detention activity involving Ms. Brown;
8. Any body-worn camera footage recorded by Winchester Police Department officers during the arrest of Robin Brown on January 25, 2023, including approximately 10 minutes prior to the initial physical or verbal contact through her transport or transfer to custody.
9. Documentation reflecting the date and time of her release from custody or transfer to another agency, including associated forms.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Mike Bregenzer

Good Afternoon,

At this time your request for records regarding Robin Brown will be denied. As of 2021 KRS 61.872(2)(a) has been amended to read;
-Any resident of the Commonwealth shall have the right to inspect public records. The official custodian may require a written application, signed by the applicant and with his or her name printed legibly on the application, describing the records to be inspected. The official custodian may require the applicant to provide a statement in the written application of the manner in which the applicant is a resident of the Commonwealth under KRS 61.870(10)(a) to (f).
Under this statute you do not qualify as a resident of the Commonwealth of Kentucky where your business is located in Boston MA and you are not an individual residing within the Commonwealth, you are not a domestic business with a location in the Commonwealth, you are not a foreign business entity, you are not employed and work for a location within the Commonwealth, you are not a business or entity that owns real property within the Commonwealth, there is also no indication that you are requesting this on the behalf of a qualifying individual.

You also do not qualify as a news-gathering organization as defined in KRS 189.635(8)
(a) The report shall be made available to a news-gathering organization, solely for the purpose of publishing or broadcasting the news. The news-gathering organization shall not use or distribute the report, or knowingly allow its use or distribution, for a commercial purpose other than the news-gathering organization's publication or broadcasting of the information in the report.
(b) For the purposes of this subsection:
1."News-gathering organization" includes:
a. A newspaper or periodical if it:
i. Is published at least fifty (50) of fifty-two (52) weeks during a calendar year;
ii. Contains at least twenty-five percent (25%) news content in each issue or no more than seventy-five percent (75%) advertising content in any issue in the calendar year; and
iii. Contains news of general interest to its readers that can include news stories, editorials, sports, weddings, births, and death notices;
b. A television or radio station with a valid broadcast license issued by the Federal Communications Commission;
c. A news organization that broadcasts over a multichannel video programming service as defined in KRS 136.602;
d. A Web site published by or affiliated with any entity described in subdivision a., b., or c. of this subparagraph;
e. An online-only newspaper or magazine that publishes news or opinion of interest to a general audience and is not affiliated with any entity described in subparagraph 2. of this paragraph; and
f. Any other entity that publishes news content by any means to the general public or to members of a particular profession or occupational group; and
2."News-gathering organization" does not include any product or publication with the primary purpose of distributing advertising or of publishing names and other personal identifying information concerning parties to motor vehicle accidents which may be used to solicit for services covered under Subtitle 39 of KRS Chapter 304.



Furthermore the Winchester Police Department is not the arresting agency and this request would have to be submitted to the FBI for release.

